..: DESCRiPTiON :..

HWMonitor is a hardware monitoring program that reads PC systems
main health sensors: voltages, temperatures, fans speed.

The program handles the most common sensor chips, like ITE IT87
series, most Winbond ICs, and others. In addition, it can read
modern CPUs on-die core thermal sensors, as well has hard drives
temperature via S.M.A.R.T, and video card GPU temperature.
Special hardware monitors such as abit uGuru and Gigabyte ODIN
power supplies serie are supported too.

In comparison to its classic counterpart, HWMonitor Pro adds the
following features:
* Remote Monitoring - Watch the sensors of one or several distant
PCs through a simple TCP/IP connection.
* Graph Generator - Save monitoring data and generate logging
graphs as bitmap files.
* Improved Interface - Sensors in system tray, editable sensors
labels ...
* PWM Control - Fan PWM control (for ESA compliant devices).
